node.text: From day one this was a blunder, and there will be a reckoning for those who caused it. Unfortunately we can’t change the past, but we can take action to correct mistakes. Republican veterans rallied today to demand we vote on such action, but Pelosi struck it down. The Biden administration needs to stop running victory laps and make it a priority to get every last American home. That should be non-negotiable. I wish Democrats agreed.

node.text:
Republicans are here demanding unanimous consent (a procedural mechanism) for a bill to be immediately brought to the floor. This bill would require this administration to give us accountability of how many Americans are left behind, a plan to get them out, a plan to get our equipment, and demand that we do NOT recognize the Taliban as a legitimate government. 

We will see if Pelosi will allow it. Unfortunately we don’t expect she will.

node.text: The press will say “we ended America’s longest war.” But that’s a lie. Always was. We didn’t end a war. They’ll still keep fighting us and they’ll have more weapons and cash to do it. We didn’t end a war, we just gave up a strategic position from which to fight it.
